This paper deals with a machine learning problem of sparse quadratic regression, which involves modeling the response as a linear function of quadratic terms of the features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the theory and applications of machine learning algorithms. The paper also involves optimization techniques to solve the problem efficiently, which suggests the possibility of belonging to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also deals with high-dimensional problems, which suggests the possibility of belonging to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
